## ğŸ’¬ Comments, Escape Sequences & Print

### ğŸ’¡ Comments

* Use `#` for single-line comments
* Use `'''` or `"""` for multi-line comments

```python
# This is a comment
''' This is
a multi-line comment '''
```

> Shortcut: `Ctrl + /` to toggle comments

---

### ğŸ” Escape Sequences

Used to include special characters in strings:

| Escape | Meaning      |
| ------ | ------------ |
| `\n`   | Newline      |
| `\t`   | Tab          |
| `\\`   | Backslash    |
| `\"`   | Double quote |
| `\'`   | Single quote |

---

### ğŸ–¨ï¸ The `print()` Function

```python
print("Hello", "World", sep="-", end="!\n")
```

* `sep` â†’ defines separator between multiple values
* `end` â†’ defines what to print at the end (default: `\n`)

